---
layout: base.njk
title: Network View
pageKey: network
permalink: /network/
---

<section class="doc-title">
  <div class="doc-title-tag">
    <span>Investor network · early preview</span>
  </div>
  <h1 class="doc-title-h1">The network of money flowing through INGO impact funds <span class="accent">— who funds whom.</span></h1>
  <p class="doc-title-sub">
    Public-source map of {{ network.stats.ingo_count }} INGO sponsors,
    {{ network.stats.fund_count }} funds,
    {{ network.stats.investor_count }} investors,
    and {{ network.stats.portco_count }} portfolio companies
    ({{ network.stats.edge_count }} edges).
    Coverage so far: Mercy Corps Ventures, AgDevCo, Kiva Refugee Investment Fund.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="sec">

  <details class="network-help">
    <summary><strong>How to read this</strong> <span class="muted">— click to expand</span></summary>
    <div class="network-help-body">

      <p class="network-thesis">
        INGOs raising their first impact-fund close struggle because the visible "impact LPs" are crowded.
        The bigger lead-gen opportunity is <em>generalist investors who already touch impact via co-investments</em>
        — they look like outsiders on a list of impact funders, but they have already deployed capital alongside
        impact funds at the portfolio level. This view maps that network: who funds whom, and where the same
        investor entity shows up in more than one position. The richer the graph, the easier it is to surface
        warm leads.
      </p>

      <div class="legend-grid">
        <div class="legend-col">
          <h4>What you're looking at</h4>
          <ul class="legend-list">
            <li><span class="lg-shape lg-ingo"></span> <b>Parent NGO</b> that runs an impact fund</li>
            <li><span class="lg-shape lg-fund"></span> <b>An impact fund</b></li>
            <li><span class="lg-shape lg-portco lg-portco-mcv"></span><span class="lg-shape lg-portco lg-portco-agdevco"></span><span class="lg-shape lg-portco lg-portco-kiva"></span> <b>A company a fund invested in.</b> Colour shows which fund.</li>
            <li><span class="lg-shape lg-investor lg-dfi"></span> <b>Development finance institution (DFI)</b> (e.g. BII, IFC, US DFC, Norfund)</li>
            <li><span class="lg-shape lg-investor lg-vc"></span> <b>VC / private fund</b> (e.g. Andreessen Horowitz, Coinbase Ventures, LowerCarbon Capital)</li>
            <li><span class="lg-shape lg-investor lg-foundation"></span> <b>Foundation</b> (e.g. Gates Foundation)</li>
            <li><span class="lg-shape lg-investor lg-family"></span> <b>Family office</b> (private wealth)</li>
            <li><span class="lg-shape lg-investor lg-government"></span> <b>Government agency</b> (e.g. USAID)</li>
            <li><span class="lg-shape lg-investor lg-other"></span> <b>Other</b> (donor-advised funds, wealth advisors, mixed)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="legend-col">
          <h4>Lines between them</h4>
          <ul class="legend-list">
            <li><span class="lg-edge lg-edge-sponsors"></span> <b>NGO runs this fund</b> (the fund is the NGO's impact-investment arm)</li>
            <li><span class="lg-edge lg-edge-investment"></span> <b>Fund invested in a company</b></li>
            <li><span class="lg-edge lg-edge-lp"></span> <b>Investor put money into a fund</b> (committed as an LP)</li>
            <li><span class="lg-edge lg-edge-co"></span> <b>Investor or funder of a company</b> (alongside or separate from an impact fund)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="legend-col">
          <h4>Try this</h4>
          <ul class="legend-list legend-tips">
            <li>Drag to pan, scroll to zoom. <b>Past 1.4× zoom</b>, all company names appear.</li>
            <li><b>Click anything</b> to see who it connects to.</li>
            <li><b>Search "BII", "Gates", "Soros"</b> to find a specific investor.</li>
            <li>Untick a fund under <b>"Which funds"</b> to isolate the others.</li>
            <li>Untick <b>"Fund invested in a company"</b> to focus on who funds the funds.</li>
            <li>Untick all but <b>"Family offices"</b> to see only family-office investors.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="muted network-caveats">
        Caveats: portfolio attribution for Kiva is umbrella-level (KRIF is one of several Kiva vehicles).
        Acumen funds are temporarily blocked behind a Cloudflare bot challenge.
        Most portcos don't yet have country/sector populated — operator review pending.
      </p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <div class="story-presets">
    <span class="preset-label">Quick views:</span>
    <button data-preset="lp">Who funds the INGO-backed funds</button>
    <button data-preset="invest">Where INGO-backed funds invest</button>
    <button data-preset="coinvestors">Non-INGO-backed funds investing in the portfolio companies of INGO-backed funds</button>
    <button data-preset="all" class="preset-reset">Show everything</button>
  </div>

  <div class="network-controls">
    <fieldset class="ctrl-group">
      <legend>Which relationships</legend>
      <label><input type="checkbox" data-edge="sponsors" checked> NGO runs a fund</label>
      <label><input type="checkbox" data-edge="lp" checked> Investor put money into a fund</label>
      <label><input type="checkbox" data-edge="investment" checked> Fund invested in a company</label>
      <label><input type="checkbox" data-edge="co-investor" checked> Other investor / funder of a company</label>
    </fieldset>

    <fieldset class="ctrl-group">
      <legend>Investor / funder kinds</legend>
      <label><input type="checkbox" data-itype="dfi" checked> Development finance institutions (DFIs)</label>
      <label><input type="checkbox" data-itype="vc" checked> VC / private funds</label>
      <label><input type="checkbox" data-itype="foundation" checked> Foundations</label>
      <label><input type="checkbox" data-itype="family-office" checked> Family offices</label>
      <label><input type="checkbox" data-itype="government" checked> Government agencies</label>
      <label><input type="checkbox" data-itype="other" checked> Other</label>
    </fieldset>

    <fieldset class="ctrl-group ctrl-funds">
      <legend>Which funds</legend>
      <label class="ctrl-master"><input type="checkbox" id="filter-ingo-only"> Only INGO-backed</label>

      <div class="ctrl-fund-section">
        <div class="ctrl-fund-section-title">INGO-backed</div>
        <div class="ctrl-fund-list">
          {% for node in network.nodes %}
            {% if node.type == 'fund' and node.ingo_slug %}
              <label><input type="checkbox" data-fund="{{ node.id | replace('fund:', '') }}" data-ingo-backed="true" checked> {{ node.name }}</label>
            {% endif %}
          {% endfor %}
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="ctrl-fund-section">
        <div class="ctrl-fund-section-title">Non-INGO-backed</div>
        <div class="ctrl-fund-list">
          {% for node in network.nodes %}
            {% if node.type == 'fund' and not node.ingo_slug %}
              <label><input type="checkbox" data-fund="{{ node.id | replace('fund:', '') }}" data-ingo-backed="false" checked> {{ node.name }}</label>
            {% endif %}
          {% endfor %}
        </div>
      </div>
    </fieldset>

    <fieldset class="ctrl-group ctrl-search">
      <legend>Find by name</legend>
      <input type="search" id="filter-search" placeholder="e.g. Gates, BII, Wasoko" />
    </fieldset>

    <fieldset class="ctrl-group">
      <legend>Layout</legend>
      <button id="layout-cose">Spread out</button>
      <button id="layout-concentric">Layer by role</button>
      <button id="reset-view">Reset zoom</button>
    </fieldset>
  </div>

  <div id="selection-info" class="muted"></div>
  <div id="cy" style="width:100%; height:75vh; min-height:600px; border:1px solid #2c2c2c; background:#0e0f12;"></div>
  <div id="node-details" class="network-details" hidden></div>
</section>

<script src="https://unpkg.com/cytoscape@3.30.2/dist/cytoscape.min.js"></script>
<script src="{{ '/assets/js/network-data.js' | url }}"></script>

<script>
  const NETWORK = window.NETWORK;
  if (!NETWORK) {
    document.getElementById('cy').innerHTML = '<p style="color:#fa3;padding:1rem;">network-data.js failed to load. Run <code>python -m network.dashboard_prep.prep_scripts.build_network_json</code> and rebuild.</p>';
    throw new Error('NETWORK data not loaded');
  }

  const elements = [
    ...NETWORK.nodes.map(n => ({ data: { id: n.id, label: n.name, ...n } })),
    ...NETWORK.edges.map(e => ({ data: { source: e.source, target: e.target, kind: e.kind } }))
  ];

  const cy = cytoscape({
    container: document.getElementById('cy'),
    elements,
    style: [
      {
        selector: 'node',
        style: {
          'label': 'data(label)',
          'color': '#d4d4d4',
          'font-size': '11px',
          'text-valign': 'center',
          'text-halign': 'center',
          'text-wrap': 'wrap',
          'text-max-width': '120px',
          'border-width': 1,
          'border-color': '#1a1a1a',
        }
      },
      { selector: 'node[type="ingo"]', style: { 'background-color': '#3a8c3a', 'shape': 'round-rectangle', 'width': 70, 'height': 30, 'font-weight': 'bold' } },
      { selector: 'node[type="fund"]', style: { 'background-color': '#3a78c4', 'shape': 'round-rectangle', 'width': 90, 'height': 34, 'font-weight': 'bold' } },
      { selector: 'node[type="investor"]', style: { 'background-color': '#c4a83a', 'shape': 'diamond', 'width': 36, 'height': 36, 'font-size': '10px', 'font-weight': 'bold' } },
      { selector: 'node[type="investor"][investor_type="dfi"]',           style: { 'background-color': '#d04848' } },
      { selector: 'node[type="investor"][investor_type="vc"]',            style: { 'background-color': '#3acaa8' } },
      { selector: 'node[type="investor"][investor_type="foundation"]',    style: { 'background-color': '#c4a83a' } },
      { selector: 'node[type="investor"][investor_type="family-office"]', style: { 'background-color': '#a85ad0' } },
      { selector: 'node[type="investor"][investor_type="other"]',         style: { 'background-color': '#888888' } },
      { selector: 'node[type="investor"][investor_type="government"]',    style: { 'background-color': '#3a8cc4' } },
      { selector: 'node[type="portco"]', style: { 'shape': 'ellipse', 'width': 14, 'height': 14, 'background-color': '#777', 'label': '', 'border-width': 0 } },
      { selector: 'node[type="portco"][parent_fund_slug="mercy-corps-ventures"]',          style: { 'background-color': '#e07b5a' } },
      { selector: 'node[type="portco"][parent_fund_slug="agdevco-smallholder-development-unit"]', style: { 'background-color': '#5ae0a5' } },
      { selector: 'node[type="portco"][parent_fund_slug="kiva-refugee-investment-fund"]',  style: { 'background-color': '#a05ae0' } },
      { selector: 'node[type="portco"].labelled', style: { 'label': 'data(label)', 'font-size': '10px', 'color': '#d4d4d4', 'text-background-color': '#0e0f12', 'text-background-opacity': 0.9, 'text-background-padding': '2px', 'z-index': 10 } },
      { selector: 'node.searched', style: { 'border-color': '#fa3', 'border-width': 3 } },
      { selector: 'node:selected', style: { 'border-color': '#fa3', 'border-width': 3 } },
      {
        selector: 'edge',
        style: {
          'width': 0.8,
          'line-color': '#3a3a3a',
          'curve-style': 'bezier',
          'target-arrow-shape': 'triangle',
          'target-arrow-color': '#3a3a3a',
          'arrow-scale': 0.6,
        }
      },
      { selector: 'edge[kind="sponsors"]',    style: { 'line-color': '#3a8c3a', 'target-arrow-color': '#3a8c3a', 'width': 1.5 } },
      { selector: 'edge[kind="investment"]',  style: { 'line-color': '#3a3a3a' } },
      { selector: 'edge[kind="lp"]',          style: { 'line-color': '#c4a83a', 'target-arrow-color': '#c4a83a', 'width': 1.5, 'line-style': 'dashed' } },
      { selector: 'edge[kind="co-investor"]', style: { 'line-color': '#9a5ad0', 'target-arrow-color': '#9a5ad0', 'width': 1.2, 'line-style': 'dotted' } },
    ],
    layout: { name: 'cose', padding: 30, nodeRepulsion: 8000, idealEdgeLength: 80, animate: false }
  });

  // Zoom-conditional portco labels: above this threshold, show all.
  const ZOOM_LABEL_THRESHOLD = 1.4;
  function syncPortcoLabels() {
    const showAll = cy.zoom() >= ZOOM_LABEL_THRESHOLD;
    cy.batch(() => {
      cy.nodes('[type="portco"]').forEach(n => {
        if (showAll || n.hasClass('hovered') || n.selected()) {
          n.addClass('labelled');
        } else {
          n.removeClass('labelled');
        }
      });
    });
  }
  cy.on('zoom', syncPortcoLabels);
  cy.on('mouseover', 'node[type="portco"]', evt => { evt.target.addClass('hovered'); syncPortcoLabels(); });
  cy.on('mouseout',  'node[type="portco"]', evt => { evt.target.removeClass('hovered'); syncPortcoLabels(); });

  cy.ready(() => { cy.fit(null, 30); });

  // ---- Filtering ----
  //
  // Mental model: the user picks relationships (edges) they care about. A
  // node shows iff it has at least one visible relationship touching it. A
  // fund also shows even with no edges if its fund-filter is on (so the
  // catalogue presence is visible). Search hides anything that doesn't match.

  function readBoxes(attr) {
    const out = new Set();
    document.querySelectorAll(`input[type="checkbox"][data-${attr}]`).forEach(el => {
      if (el.checked) out.add(el.dataset[attr]);
    });
    return out;
  }

  function fundSlugForEdge(e) {
    const k = e.data('kind');
    const s = e.source(), t = e.target();
    if (k === 'sponsors')   return t.id().replace(/^fund:/, '');
    if (k === 'lp')         return t.id().replace(/^fund:/, '');
    if (k === 'investment') return s.id().replace(/^fund:/, '');
    if (k === 'co-investor') return t.data('parent_fund_slug') || null;
    return null;
  }

  function investorEndpointItype(e) {
    const k = e.data('kind');
    if (k === 'lp' || k === 'co-investor') {
      const inv = (e.source().data('type') === 'investor') ? e.source() : e.target();
      return inv.data('investor_type') || 'other';
    }
    return null;
  }

  function applyFilters() {
    const enabledEdges  = readBoxes('edge');
    const enabledItypes = readBoxes('itype');
    const enabledFunds  = readBoxes('fund');
    const search = (document.getElementById('filter-search').value || '').trim().toLowerCase();

    // Pass 1: which edges pass all filters (kind + investor-type + fund)
    const visibleEdges = new Set();
    cy.edges().forEach(e => {
      if (!enabledEdges.has(e.data('kind'))) return;

      const itype = investorEndpointItype(e);
      if (itype && !enabledItypes.has(itype)) return;

      const fundSlug = fundSlugForEdge(e);
      if (fundSlug && !enabledFunds.has(fundSlug)) return;

      visibleEdges.add(e.id());
    });

    cy.batch(() => {
      // Pass 2: node visibility
      cy.nodes().forEach(n => {
        const t = n.data('type');

        // Has at least one visible edge?
        let touchesVisible = n.connectedEdges().some(e => visibleEdges.has(e.id()));

        // Funds always render when their per-fund toggle is on, even with no edges.
        if (t === 'fund') {
          const slug = n.id().replace(/^fund:/, '');
          if (enabledFunds.has(slug)) touchesVisible = true;
        }

        // Search filter overrides everything.
        let show = touchesVisible;
        const name = (n.data('name') || '').toLowerCase();
        if (search) {
          if (!name.includes(search)) show = false;
        }

        n.style('display', show ? 'element' : 'none');

        if (search && name.includes(search)) {
          n.addClass('searched');
        } else {
          n.removeClass('searched');
        }
      });

      // Pass 3: apply edge visibility (and re-hide edges whose endpoints got hidden by search)
      cy.edges().forEach(e => {
        let show = visibleEdges.has(e.id());
        if (show && search) {
          if (e.source().style('display') === 'none' || e.target().style('display') === 'none') {
            show = false;
          }
        }
        e.style('display', show ? 'element' : 'none');
      });
    });

    // Visible-count indicator.
    const visibleCount = cy.nodes().filter(n => n.style('display') !== 'none').length;
    const totalCount = cy.nodes().length;
    document.getElementById('selection-info').textContent =
      visibleCount === totalCount ? '' : `Showing ${visibleCount} of ${totalCount} entities`;
  }

  // ---- Presets ----
  // Each preset configures the filter checkboxes and re-runs applyFilters.
  // INGO-only is forced on for the 3 stories; off for "Show everything".
  const PRESETS = {
    invest:      { edges: ['sponsors', 'investment'],                          ingoOnly: true  },
    lp:          { edges: ['sponsors', 'lp'],                                   ingoOnly: true  },
    coinvestors: { edges: ['sponsors', 'investment', 'co-investor'],            ingoOnly: true  },
    all:         { edges: ['sponsors', 'lp', 'investment', 'co-investor'],      ingoOnly: false },
  };

  function applyPreset(name) {
    const p = PRESETS[name];
    if (!p) return;
    // Edges
    document.querySelectorAll('input[type="checkbox"][data-edge]').forEach(el => {
      el.checked = p.edges.includes(el.dataset.edge);
    });
    // Investor types: always all on
    document.querySelectorAll('input[type="checkbox"][data-itype]').forEach(el => {
      el.checked = true;
    });
    // INGO-only toggle
    const ingoOnly = document.getElementById('filter-ingo-only');
    ingoOnly.checked = p.ingoOnly;
    syncIngoOnly();
    applyFilters();
  }
  document.querySelectorAll('.story-presets button[data-preset]').forEach(btn => {
    btn.addEventListener('click', () => applyPreset(btn.dataset.preset));
  });

  // ---- INGO-backed only master toggle ----
  function syncIngoOnly() {
    const ingoOnly = document.getElementById('filter-ingo-only').checked;
    document.querySelectorAll('input[type="checkbox"][data-fund]').forEach(box => {
      const isIngo = box.dataset.ingoBacked === 'true';
      if (ingoOnly) {
        box.checked = isIngo;
        box.disabled = !isIngo;
      } else {
        box.disabled = false;
        box.checked = true;
      }
    });
  }
  document.getElementById('filter-ingo-only').addEventListener('change', () => {
    syncIngoOnly();
    applyFilters();
  });

  // Wire filters
  document.querySelectorAll('.network-controls input[type="checkbox"]').forEach(el => {
    el.addEventListener('change', applyFilters);
  });
  document.getElementById('filter-search').addEventListener('input', applyFilters);

  // Layout buttons
  document.getElementById('layout-cose').addEventListener('click', () => {
    cy.layout({ name: 'cose', padding: 30, nodeRepulsion: 8000, idealEdgeLength: 80, animate: false }).run();
  });
  document.getElementById('layout-concentric').addEventListener('click', () => {
    cy.layout({
      name: 'concentric',
      concentric: n => ({ ingo: 4, investor: 3, fund: 2, portco: 1 }[n.data('type')] ?? 0),
      levelWidth: () => 1,
      padding: 30,
      animate: false,
    }).run();
  });
  document.getElementById('reset-view').addEventListener('click', () => cy.fit(null, 30));

  // Click handler — node details panel
  const details = document.getElementById('node-details');
  cy.on('tap', 'node', evt => {
    const d = evt.target.data();
    let html = `<h3>${d.name}</h3><p class="muted">${d.type}${d.investor_type ? ' · ' + d.investor_type : ''}</p>`;
    if (d.country) html += `<p>Country: ${d.country}</p>`;
    if (d.website) html += `<p>Website: <a href="${d.website}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">${d.website}</a></p>`;
    if (d.thesis_tags) html += `<p>Thesis: ${d.thesis_tags}</p>`;
    if (d.fund_type) html += `<p>Fund type: ${d.fund_type}</p>`;
    if (d.impact_focus) html += `<p>Impact focus: ${d.impact_focus}</p>`;
    const neighbors = evt.target.neighborhood('node');
    if (neighbors.length) {
      html += `<p>Connected to ${neighbors.length} entities:</p><ul>`;
      neighbors.forEach(n => { html += `<li>${n.data('name')} <span class="muted">(${n.data('type')})</span></li>`; });
      html += `</ul>`;
    }
    details.innerHTML = html;
    details.hidden = false;
  });
  cy.on('tap', evt => {
    if (evt.target === cy) {
      details.hidden = true;
    }
  });
</script>

<style>
  /* Help / legend */
  .network-help { margin: 1rem 0 1.5rem; background: #0e0f12; border: 1px solid #2c2c2c; padding: 0.5rem 1rem; }
  .network-help summary { cursor: pointer; padding: 0.4rem 0; font-size: 1rem; }
  .network-help-body { padding-top: 0.5rem; }
  .network-thesis { max-width: 70rem; margin: 0 0 1rem 0; line-height: 1.5; }
  .network-caveats { margin-top: 1rem; font-size: 0.85rem; }

  .legend-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr)); gap: 1.5rem; margin: 1rem 0; }
  .legend-col h4 { margin: 0 0 0.5rem 0; font-size: 0.9rem; color: #aaa; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; }
  .legend-list { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; }
  .legend-list li { padding: 0.25rem 0; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.4; }
  .legend-tips li { padding: 0.3rem 0; }

  /* Legend node swatches */
  .lg-shape { display: inline-block; vertical-align: middle; margin-right: 0.4rem; }
  .lg-ingo  { width: 28px; height: 14px; background: #3a8c3a; border-radius: 4px; }
  .lg-fund  { width: 32px; height: 14px; background: #3a78c4; border-radius: 4px; }
  .lg-portco { width: 10px; height: 10px; border-radius: 50%; }
  .lg-portco-mcv     { background: #e07b5a; }
  .lg-portco-agdevco { background: #5ae0a5; }
  .lg-portco-kiva    { background: #a05ae0; }
  .lg-investor { width: 12px; height: 12px; transform: rotate(45deg); }
  .lg-dfi        { background: #d04848; }
  .lg-vc         { background: #3acaa8; }
  .lg-foundation { background: #c4a83a; }
  .lg-family     { background: #a85ad0; }
  .lg-government { background: #3a8cc4; }
  .lg-other      { background: #888; }

  /* Legend edge samples */
  .lg-edge { display: inline-block; width: 28px; height: 0; vertical-align: middle; margin-right: 0.5rem; border-top-width: 2px; border-top-style: solid; }
  .lg-edge-sponsors    { border-color: #3a8c3a; }
  .lg-edge-investment  { border-color: #3a3a3a; }
  .lg-edge-lp          { border-color: #c4a83a; border-top-style: dashed; }
  .lg-edge-co          { border-color: #9a5ad0; border-top-style: dotted; border-top-width: 3px; }

  /* Story presets row */
  .story-presets { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem; padding: 0.5rem 0; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .preset-label { color: #aaa; font-size: 0.85rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; }
  .story-presets button { background: #2a3a4a; color: #cfdbe6; border: 1px solid #3a4a5e; padding: 0.4rem 0.8rem; cursor: pointer; font-family: inherit; font-size: 0.9rem; border-radius: 3px; }
  .story-presets button:hover { background: #344a60; border-color: #5a7896; }
  .story-presets button.preset-reset { background: #1a1a1a; color: #aaa; border-color: #333; }
  .story-presets button.preset-reset:hover { background: #222; border-color: #555; }

